<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="6iobkp" data-video-descrip="Naofumi finds himself transported to another world where he's expected to help save the world from strange portals in the air that allow monsters to invade the world. After he is falsely accused of rape, he insists on being sent back home only to learn he can't be sent home until the Waves are defeated." data-video-title="The Rising of the Shield Hero" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/6iobkp_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/6iobkp.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/TrappedInAnotherWorld" data-video-tropename="Trapped in Another World" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="LightNovel/TheRisingOfTheShieldHero,Recap/TheRisingOfTheShieldHeroS1E1TheShieldHero" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/6iobkp.jpg">
